media$title.$t: Mortgage Company doesn't accept the Video Relay Calls

media$description.$t:
Mortgage Company doesn't accept the Video Relay Calls


Ken Davis, a deaf borrower, is suing Ocwen Loan Servicing, LLC, for a violation of the Americans with Disabilities Act. He had a hard time to reach his Mortgage Company by Video Relay Service for two months. It messed and ruined his mortgage payment. He got a letter from the mortgage company and said that they want him to do the foreclosure. He is seeking an attorney and files a lawsuit. 

Your information and Feedback will help him. 

Thanks for your Support!
